    "patch_code": "private static Set<String> BUILTIN_FUNCTIONS_WITH_NO_IDEFFECTS =\n   Sets.newHashSet(\"parseInt\", \"parseFloat\", \"escape\", \"unescape\");\n\nstatic boolean functionCallHasSideEffects(Node callNode, AbstractCompiler compiler) {\nif (!callNode.isMethodInvocation()) {\nreturn false;\n}\n\n// Check for built-in method calls such as parseInt etc... These methods don't have side effects.\nNode nameNode = callNode.getQualifiedNamePrefix();\nif (nameNode != null && nameNode.getType() == Token.IDENTIFIER) {\nString name = nameNode.getString();\nif (BUILTIN_FUNCTIONS_WITH_NO_IDEFFECTS.contains(name)) {\nreturn false;\n}\n}\nreturn true;\n}",
